V Randy
Was checking out this link last couple of days. Nice walleyes and sturgeon. Better view than last year. Checked out the eagle cams as well but not much happening there.
Cool! I just saw a bunch of Walleye then a turtle!
In the few min. I watched it there were a few big ones going by!  I need to bookmark it as I check it out every spring it gets posted.
Love that cam!  Thanks for posting!
I JUST SAW A 35" EYE!  there's a big school going by.
Wow I love it.
That's a walleye HOT spot!!!
is the camera down?
It's dark out ...
hahahahahahahahahahahahahahahaha
Just kidding .........  It goes out from time to time .... It went out tonight at around 7:45.....   Randy
Just little guys right now. wolf river.tiff
Fairly constant stream of walleye. Saw a smallmouth and carp go by as well. Kinda like scuba diving there.
i just saw your carp.
A very deformed tumorous Walleye was about yesterday ... Looked like someone glued a whole whack of gum balls to him....
I saw a little sunfish (bluegill) this morning.
Smallmouth just went by, were is wolf river?
And now a sucker!

This river is in Wisconsin and flows into Lake Michigan.  Little murkier and less active today but saw usual walleyes and a pike. A white sucker went slowly along bottom and posed in front of camera for a minute.
Carp  just ran into the camera!
